<div style="text-align: left; font-size: 14px; max-width: 770px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
  <h1>Reserving Classes for Certain Students</h1>
  <p>There are 3 different ways to restrict classes to be only for certain students.</p>
  <h2>Option 1</h2>
  <p>If you don't need the course to be visible on the public site, the simplest
    way to block unwanted registrations is just to "un-publish" the course. Then
    it will just be available to Administrators, but the public won't be able to
    see it. Of course, that will prevent the students to enroll themselves, so it
    may not work for every situation.</p>
  <h2>Option 2</h2>
  <p>If the course type is set to to "School", rather than "Public", it will
    have special messages throughout the registration process. For example, on
    the "Find A Course" page, there will be a special message under the Enroll
    button, like this:</p>
  <img src="<?php echo A25_Link::to('/administrator/images/Documentation/school_find_course.png')?>" />
  <p>Then if they click Enroll, they will see this message at the top of the screen:</p>
  <img src="<?php echo A25_Link::to('/administrator/images/Documentation/school_enroll.png')?>" />
  <p>However, this does not actually block anyone from enrolling. The wrong
    person could still enroll if they ignore the messages, although that doesn't
    seem to happen too often.</p>
  <h2>Option 3</h2>
  <p style="font-size: 12px; color: #666; background-color: #efefff; padding: 12px;">
      This is an <i>optional</i> feature which is not enabled by default.  If
      you would like it turned on for your website, please email the
      website developer, Jonathan Albright, at
      <a href="mailto:jonathan@appdevl.net">jonathan@appdevl.net</a>.
  </p>
  <p>If you want to put a password on the class, we can install the <a href=
    "<?php echo A25_Link::to('/administrator/documentation/organization-registration-code')?>
    ">Registration Code for Organizations</a> extension for you. Then, the class
    will ask for a password when they click Enroll, like this:</p>
  <img src="<?php echo A25_Link::to('/administrator/images/Documentation/registration_code.png')?>" />
  <p>For more details, see the documentation for <a href=
    "<?php echo A25_Link::to('/administrator/documentation/organization-registration-code')?>
    ">Registration Code for Organizations</a>.</p>
</div>
